    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">Laplacian</ref> to smoothly deform a region preserving mesh fine details. How to use:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>Initialize <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian" kindref="compound">Laplacian</ref> for the region being deformed, here region properties are remembered.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Change positions of some vertices within the region and call fixVertex for them.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Optionally call <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian_1a3e7bb340acaa3ef81fe7ed9f5eaaf226" kindref="member">updateSolver()</ref></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Call <ref refid="classMR_1_1Laplacian_1a1a99ff3fbda2af6c118c5bb00a99d5d1" kindref="member">apply()</ref> to change the remaining vertices within the region Then steps 1-4 or 2-4 can be repeated. <programlisting filename="cpp-samples/LaplacianDeformation.cpp"></programlisting> </para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
